transcript_text: I find that a lot of people have trouble developing the mind muscle connection with the side delts  or doing lateral raises without using too much trap. To fix that try fully protracting your  shoulders and flexing your lats before and throughout the entire set as I do here.  This should reduce trap involvement and mitigate some movement of the shoulder blades.  Make sure you don't allow your shoulders to roll forward though. In other words your traps shouldn't  be flexed. Some other pieces of advice are to try using lighter weight, cheating less with the  movement and doing one arm at a time until you can develop that proper mind muscle connection.  I also wouldn't recommend chasing progressive overload with lateral raise variations  and focusing more on metabolic fatigue if during each set.
